    "summary": "Soon graduating from a Food Technology Master (with a specialization in Product Design) of Wageningen University, I am looking for a junior position in Research and Innovation. Available from September 2021\n-\n\"Be where the world is going\" is the sentence I have tried to apply to my journey in food sciences and innovation.\n\nThis journey started with an engineering degree in Food & Health at Unilasalle Beauvais- France. There I learnt a lot about food quality, but also the deep link between food, our health and the different world issues. For my first internship, I had the privilege to work on prebiotics, involved in so many mechanisms that are not yet all explored. Then, the second internship was on the quality department of a pasta factory that was trying to make little impact on our planet. Finally, my last student project, a very human and unique experience, was to work on innovative nutritherapie and culinary workshops with children with autism. \n\nThis degree was then completed with the Food Technology Master of Wageningen. The chosen specialization, Product Design, has made me acquired great competences in project management, creativity, communication and, of course, food sciences. The different student projects were the translation of the consumer needs to food attributes and design. This degree have made my interest to innovation, sustainability and health grown even more. \n\nFinally, I am currently on my master internship at Danone Nutricia, in the Research and Development team. My project is about optimizing some infant nutrition products. Innovation for a better health is the fuel of this project and I am very proud to be responsible of it. \n\nI can't wait to walk a bit with you on this adventure on Food R&D\n\n\nKeywords: Research and Development (R&D), Product Development (NPD), Culinary Arts, Product Formulation, , Sensory Analysis, Sustainability, Food and Health, Nutrition, Microbiology\n",
